snippet: Ending years of uncertainty, the Dutch defense ministry said the country would replace its fleet of F-16 jets with F-35s made by Lockheed Martin but would buy fewer than planned.
abstract: Dutch defense ministry, ending years of uncertainty, says it will replace its fleet of F-16 fighter jets with F-35s made by Lockheed Martin; will buy fewer than planned.
lead_paragraph: Ending years of uncertainty, the Dutch defense ministry said the country would replace its fleet of F-16 jets with F-35s made by Lockheed Martin but would buy fewer than planned.

headline.main: Dutch Pick F-35 Jets to Expand Aging Fleet
headline.print_headline: Dutch Pick F-35 Jets To Expand Aging Fleet
